1
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:33,408
[Solemn Oriental instrumental music]

2
00:00:33,492 --> 00:00:37,913
'HOUSE OF FLYING DAGGERS'

3
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:42,251
CHINA 859 A.D.
- The once-mighty Tang Dynasty is in decline.

4
00:00:42,501 --> 00:00:44,753
The Emperor is weak and incompetent.

5
00:00:44,837 --> 00:00:47,631
His corrupt government
no longer controls the land.

6
00:00:47,965 --> 00:00:49,299
Unrest sweeps the country.

7
00:00:49,424 --> 00:00:51,885
Village by village,
an underground alliance forms...

8
00:00:52,261 --> 00:00:55,472
'The House of Flying Daggers'.

9
00:00:55,764 --> 00:00:57,558
Based near the Imperial Capital,

10
00:00:57,641 --> 00:01:00,102
The House Of Flying Daggers
moves in the shadows.

11
00:01:00,435 --> 00:01:02,521
Stealing from the rich to give to the poor,

12
00:01:02,604 --> 00:01:04,982
they earn the support and
admiration of the people.

13
00:01:05,107 --> 00:01:07,484
At the same time,
they are feared and hated

14
00:01:07,568 --> 00:01:09,903
by their bitter rivals...
the local deputies.

15
00:01:12,823 --> 00:01:15,701
Police Headquarters - Feng Tian County

16
00:01:18,704 --> 00:01:22,916
Capt. Leo, Capt. Jin.
We're heading out on patrol.

17
00:01:31,008 --> 00:01:33,218
We're going to be busy again.

18
00:01:33,886 --> 00:01:35,929
The Provincial Office has given us 10 days...

19
00:01:36,013 --> 00:01:38,140
to catch the new leader of the Flying Daggers.

20
00:01:38,223 --> 00:01:39,308
What?

21
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:44,730
It took us three months
to assassinate their old leader.

22
00:01:45,898 --> 00:01:47,691
Ten days? Impossible.

23
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:52,738
Have you heard of the new Peony Pavilion?

24
00:01:53,197 --> 00:01:54,323
Yes.

25
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:57,201
Does anyone know you there?

26
00:01:57,784 --> 00:02:00,412
No, I haven't been there yet.

27
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:03,498
Good, now's your chance.

28
00:02:03,707 --> 00:02:05,292
Any information?

29
00:02:06,376 --> 00:02:10,923
We suspect one of the showgirls
is a member of the Flying Daggers.

30
00:02:12,925 --> 00:02:14,885
Okay, I'll check it out.

31
00:02:17,429 --> 00:02:20,516
Entertainment House - Peony Pavilion

32
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:22,434
[Women giggling]

33
00:02:22,768 --> 00:02:25,854
JIN: Pull. Pull harder.

34
00:02:26,897 --> 00:02:28,315
<i>Pull harder.</i>

35
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:30,859
[All laughing]

36
00:02:31,944 --> 00:02:33,237
GIRL: Come on.

37
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:36,114
[Light Oriental instrumental music]

38
00:02:40,369 --> 00:02:41,828
[Jin exclaiming]

39
00:02:48,752 --> 00:02:50,587
That's it. I'm done.

40
00:02:51,547 --> 00:02:53,298
- Madam!
- I'm coming.

41
00:02:53,507 --> 00:02:55,175
JIN: Madam.
MADAM: Here I am.

42
00:02:58,470 --> 00:03:00,556
What can I do for you, sir?

43
00:03:01,390 --> 00:03:03,559
I heard you have a new girl.

44
00:03:04,059 --> 00:03:06,270
You're well informed.

45
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:10,649
Is she pretty?

46
00:03:10,941 --> 00:03:12,526
She's quite a beauty.

47
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:14,194
Bring her to me.

48
00:03:15,112 --> 00:03:16,864
[Clearing throat]

49
00:03:31,128 --> 00:03:34,339
There is one thing you need to know.

50
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:36,633
What's that?

51
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:38,886
The girl is blind.

52
00:03:40,596 --> 00:03:41,763
Blind?

53
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:45,642
Then she must be special.

54
00:03:45,893 --> 00:03:47,311
I'm curious.

55
00:03:51,815 --> 00:03:54,818
[Light Oriental instrumental music resumes]

56
00:03:55,319 --> 00:03:58,447
[Women chattering and laughing
in the distance]

57
00:04:18,675 --> 00:04:20,427
[Grunting questioningly]

58
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:31,939
How did you lose your sight?

59
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:34,650
I was born blind.

60
00:04:35,984 --> 00:04:38,403
Why would a blind girl work here?

61
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:41,657
Why can't a blind girl work here?

62
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:43,075
[Chuckles]

63
00:04:43,158 --> 00:04:44,660
You're right.

64
00:04:45,827 --> 00:04:48,372
- What's your name?
- Mei.

65
00:04:50,082 --> 00:04:51,375
Mei?

66
00:04:52,668 --> 00:04:55,879
Every girl in this pavilion
has taken the name of a flower.

67
00:04:55,963 --> 00:04:57,798
Why is yours so plain?

68
00:04:58,882 --> 00:05:02,135
I don't want to compete
with those ordinary girls.

69
00:05:03,011 --> 00:05:04,680
What do you mean?

70
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:08,767
MEI: The flowers displayed here
can hardly be called flowers.

71
00:05:08,851 --> 00:05:11,436
Real flowers bloom
in the wilderness.

72
00:05:12,479 --> 00:05:14,064
[Grunting affirmatively]

73
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:15,524
well said.

74
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:21,697
If you impress me...

75
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:24,324
I'll take you
to where the real flowers grow.

76
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:30,080
What's your talent
as the top showgirl?

77
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:32,666
Dancing.

78
00:05:33,083 --> 00:05:34,501
Come closer.

79
00:06:13,582 --> 00:06:14,875
[Mei gasps]

80
00:06:21,215 --> 00:06:22,758
[Jin chucking]

81
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:25,093
Don't you know the rules?

82
00:06:31,892 --> 00:06:33,268
[bell ringing]

83
00:06:46,323 --> 00:06:47,741
[Jingling]

84
00:06:51,787 --> 00:06:54,498
[Melodious Oriental music playing]

85
00:07:29,366 --> 00:07:33,996
[Singing] A rare beauty in the North

86
00:07:34,621 --> 00:07:39,042
<i>She's the finest lady on earth</i>

87
00:07:40,085 --> 00:07:44,590
<i>A glance from her,
the whole city goes down</i>

88
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:50,220
<i>A second glance
leaves the whole nation in ruins</i>

89
00:07:50,637 --> 00:07:53,348
There exists no city or nation

90
00:07:53,432 --> 00:07:58,061
that has been more cherished

91
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:03,275
<i>than a beauty like this</i>

92
00:08:30,969 --> 00:08:35,182
A rare beauty in the North

93
00:08:36,308 --> 00:08:40,646
<i>She's the finest lady on earth</i>

94
00:08:41,688 --> 00:08:46,193
<i>A glance from her,
the whole city goes down</i>

95
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:51,865
<i>A second glance
leaves the whole nation in ruins</i>

96
00:08:52,241 --> 00:08:54,743
There exists no city or nation

97
00:08:54,993 --> 00:08:59,706
that has been more cherished

98
00:09:00,457 --> 00:09:04,336
than a beauty

99
00:09:04,461 --> 00:09:08,006
<i>like this</i>

100
00:09:11,426 --> 00:09:12,845
[Mei screams]

101
00:09:13,637 --> 00:09:15,514
[Women exclaiming in shock]

102
00:09:15,597 --> 00:09:17,182
[Mei screaming]

103
00:09:17,558 --> 00:09:19,810
SERVANT: Please calm down, sir.

104
00:09:21,770 --> 00:09:22,896
JIN: Go away.

105
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:24,690
MADAM: What's the matter?

106
00:09:25,107 --> 00:09:26,859
Please let me explain.

107
00:09:26,942 --> 00:09:28,694
MADAM: She is young and inexperienced.

108
00:09:28,777 --> 00:09:30,320
Please forgive her.

109
00:09:30,404 --> 00:09:31,780
Take her away.

110
00:09:31,864 --> 00:09:33,073
JIN: Go away.

111
00:09:33,156 --> 00:09:35,158
MADAM: Take her away.
LEO: Stop!

112
00:09:38,537 --> 00:09:39,788
MADAM: Captain.

113
00:09:40,664 --> 00:09:43,417
This is the Captain of the County.

114
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,919
JIN: To hell with the Captain!

115
00:09:46,336 --> 00:09:48,463
Outrageous! Arrest him.

116
00:09:50,716 --> 00:09:52,092
JIN: Let me go.

117
00:09:54,636 --> 00:09:56,096
Who are you?

118
00:09:56,180 --> 00:09:57,681
[Mei grunting]

119
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:01,351
How dare you! I'm the Captain.

120
00:10:02,728 --> 00:10:06,773
You're drunk and indecently dressed.

121
00:10:07,357 --> 00:10:09,151
Arrest both of them.

122
00:10:09,484 --> 00:10:12,321
JIN: Get your hands off me.

123
00:10:12,946 --> 00:10:14,156
JIN: Let me go.

124
00:10:15,032 --> 00:10:16,658
Please spare the girl, Captain.

125
00:10:16,742 --> 00:10:18,535
That man was drunk.

126
00:10:18,619 --> 00:10:20,245
It was not her fault.

127
00:10:20,329 --> 00:10:21,788
Please don't arrest her.

128
00:10:21,872 --> 00:10:24,666
Our business is new.
I rely on her to bring in guests.

129
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:27,503
How can a blind girl
be a top showgirl? Move!

130
00:10:27,586 --> 00:10:30,464
She's a dancer with rare skills.

131
00:10:30,714 --> 00:10:32,841
Please see for yourself.

132
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,805
Do you know the Echo Game?

133
00:10:39,431 --> 00:10:40,933
I played it once.

134
00:10:41,016 --> 00:10:42,351
All right.

135
00:10:42,518 --> 00:10:44,978
Perform well and I'll let you go.

136
00:10:46,146 --> 00:10:47,731
Thank you, Captain.

137
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:49,691
Go and change quickly.

138
00:10:55,989 --> 00:10:57,950
[All clamouring]

139
00:11:52,462 --> 00:11:54,214
[Rhythmic drumbeats]

140
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:58,302
ALL: Fantastic.

141
00:12:12,608 --> 00:12:14,735
[Rhythmic drumbeats]

142
00:12:15,652 --> 00:12:17,279
[Spectators cheering]

143
00:12:17,362 --> 00:12:18,739
[Chuckling]

144
00:12:19,323 --> 00:12:21,283
[Spectators applauding]

145
00:12:42,888 --> 00:12:44,973
[Rhythmic drumbeats]

146
00:12:48,185 --> 00:12:50,979
ALL: Excellent!

147
00:13:07,788 --> 00:13:09,998
[Drums rattling in succession]

148
00:13:17,881 --> 00:13:20,050
[Clattering]

149
00:13:24,763 --> 00:13:26,890
[Rhythmic drumbeats]

150
00:13:41,238 --> 00:13:43,574
[Drumbeats increase in tempo]

151
00:14:56,939 --> 00:14:59,107
[Drumbeats swell to a climax]

152
00:15:00,192 --> 00:15:01,610
[Women screaming]

153
00:15:03,070 --> 00:15:04,738
[Leo grunting]

154
00:15:10,577 --> 00:15:11,954
[Exclaiming]

155
00:15:21,296 --> 00:15:22,506
[Gasps]

156
00:15:24,466 --> 00:15:26,218
[All clamouring]

157
00:15:27,511 --> 00:15:29,137
[All screaming]

158
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:36,270
Who are you, really?

159
00:15:37,813 --> 00:15:39,857
Why do you want to kill me?

160
00:15:39,982 --> 00:15:41,567
Government running dogs...

161
00:15:41,650 --> 00:15:43,694
I wish to kill all of you!

162
00:15:47,197 --> 00:15:49,116
[Both grunting]

163
00:15:55,247 --> 00:15:56,665
[Laughing softly]

164
00:16:18,103 --> 00:16:20,814
[Gripping Oriental instrumental music]

165
00:16:26,445 --> 00:16:27,779
[Drum pounding]

166
00:16:47,090 --> 00:16:49,885
I do enjoy fighting a blind girl.

167
00:17:23,377 --> 00:17:26,296
[Gripping Oriental instrumental music
heightens]

168
00:17:38,392 --> 00:17:40,310
[Beads tinkling softly]

169
00:18:00,956 --> 00:18:03,000
[Water gurgling]

170
00:18:24,521 --> 00:18:26,356
[Leo grunting angrily]

171
00:18:27,983 --> 00:18:29,860
[Mei choking]

172
00:18:45,834 --> 00:18:47,920
POLICEMAN: We found this in her room.

173
00:19:00,474 --> 00:19:03,143
You're a member
of the Flying Daggers.

174
00:19:06,772 --> 00:19:08,607
Who's the new leader?

175
00:19:10,859 --> 00:19:13,028
LEO: Where's the new leader?

176
00:19:17,616 --> 00:19:21,328
I'll show you what We'll do to you
if you refuse to answer.

177
00:19:21,411 --> 00:19:22,663
Show her!

178
00:19:42,432 --> 00:19:44,977
In front of you is a torture device.

179
00:19:50,649 --> 00:19:52,359
[Mei grunting]

180
00:19:56,947 --> 00:19:58,991
Your head will be put here.

181
00:20:03,871 --> 00:20:05,664
Your shoulder, here.

182
00:20:06,582 --> 00:20:08,208
Your back, here.

183
00:20:09,042 --> 00:20:10,627
Your legs, here.

184
00:20:12,754 --> 00:20:14,464
[Machine creaking]

185
00:20:19,803 --> 00:20:23,432
you'll never dance again after this.

186
00:20:24,641 --> 00:20:26,351
Do you understand?

187
00:20:38,238 --> 00:20:42,284
You have one day to think it over.

188
00:20:48,290 --> 00:20:50,584
This girl reminds me of someone.

189
00:20:51,335 --> 00:20:52,461
Who?

190
00:20:54,087 --> 00:20:55,422
Rumour has it...

191
00:20:55,547 --> 00:20:59,301
the old leader's blind daughter
disappeared after his death.

192
00:21:00,010 --> 00:21:02,513
It was a heavy blow
to the Flying Daggers.

193
00:21:02,596 --> 00:21:06,558
They vowed revenge for their loss,
while searching for the girl.

194
00:21:10,979 --> 00:21:15,526
Why would the old leader's daughter
end up in a brothel?

195
00:21:17,069 --> 00:21:20,072
Who owns the Peony Pavilion?

196
00:21:21,657 --> 00:21:24,368
<i>Perhaps the Flying Daggers
have realised...</i>

197
00:21:24,451 --> 00:21:27,579
<i>we were responsible
for their old leader's death.</i>

198
00:21:27,788 --> 00:21:29,122
Forget it.

199
00:21:29,456 --> 00:21:32,292
Let's turn her over to the
Provincial Office for a reward...

200
00:21:32,376 --> 00:21:33,836
and then go out for a drink.

201
00:21:35,337 --> 00:21:37,172
I have a better idea.

202
00:21:37,381 --> 00:21:39,091
Since we have some clues...

203
00:21:39,466 --> 00:21:42,427
let's follow them through
for a bigger reward.

204
00:21:44,221 --> 00:21:45,639
Do you want me to do it?

205
00:21:45,722 --> 00:21:47,724
Of course, who else?

206
00:21:50,310 --> 00:21:53,814
All right.
This girl is a rare beauty.

207
00:21:54,439 --> 00:21:57,192
You know I love flirting with girls.

208
00:22:01,071 --> 00:22:03,949
Don't let beauty
blind your judgment.

209
00:22:04,032 --> 00:22:07,119
If I die under a skirt,
I still can flirt as a ghost.

210
00:22:08,495 --> 00:22:10,372
[Both laughing]

211
00:22:28,015 --> 00:22:30,142
[Guards grunting]

212
00:22:40,861 --> 00:22:42,654
[All grunting]

213
00:23:52,683 --> 00:23:54,101
MEI: Who are you?

214
00:23:54,601 --> 00:23:56,353
I undressed you only yesterday.

215
00:23:56,436 --> 00:23:58,689
Have you forgotten me already?

216
00:23:58,856 --> 00:24:00,691
Why did you rescue me?

217
00:24:02,359 --> 00:24:04,027
Why do you think?

218
00:24:04,987 --> 00:24:07,072
You're an exquisite flower.

219
00:24:07,322 --> 00:24:09,575
I'll do anything to help you.

220
00:24:10,033 --> 00:24:11,702
Control yourself.

221
00:24:12,494 --> 00:24:13,829
Don't worry.

222
00:24:13,954 --> 00:24:16,248
I'm no longer a guest
of the Peony Pavilion.

223
00:24:16,331 --> 00:24:17,916
JIN: You're not a showgirl anymore.

224
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:20,627
You're the daughter
of the old leader.

225
00:24:20,711 --> 00:24:22,337
What did you say?

226
00:24:22,546 --> 00:24:24,882
How many blind girls
know martial arts...

227
00:24:24,965 --> 00:24:27,176
and carry daggers like these?

228
00:24:29,011 --> 00:24:31,430
JIN: I've rescued you...

229
00:24:31,847 --> 00:24:33,849
and your daggers, as well.

230
00:24:37,477 --> 00:24:39,730
Why did you take such a risk?

231
00:24:40,272 --> 00:24:44,026
I hate the corrupt government
and admire the Flying Daggers.

232
00:24:45,903 --> 00:24:47,362
Much obliged.

233
00:24:48,864 --> 00:24:50,782
MEI: Why did we abandon the horses?

234
00:24:50,908 --> 00:24:52,576
JIN: Hoofprints can be easily tracked.

235
00:24:52,659 --> 00:24:55,120
I have two new horses hidden ahead.

236
00:24:55,245 --> 00:24:57,039
MEI: You've planned well.

237
00:24:58,165 --> 00:25:00,125
What's your name, Master?

238
00:25:00,209 --> 00:25:01,877
JIN: Just call me Wind.

239
00:25:02,377 --> 00:25:03,462
Wind?

240
00:25:03,629 --> 00:25:07,758
I wander around all alone,
come and go without a trace.

241
00:25:07,841 --> 00:25:09,635
Like a carefree wind?

242
00:25:09,718 --> 00:25:12,679
No, a playful wind.

243
00:25:12,763 --> 00:25:14,014
[Jin chuckling]

244
00:25:14,097 --> 00:25:15,807
You like to tease.

245
00:25:15,891 --> 00:25:17,851
I wonder what you look like.

246
00:25:18,101 --> 00:25:19,853
That's easy to find out.

247
00:25:19,937 --> 00:25:21,063
Here.

248
00:25:23,148 --> 00:25:24,691
Please let go.

249
00:25:25,067 --> 00:25:27,736
This isn't the Peony Pavilion.
There are no rules here.

250
00:25:27,819 --> 00:25:31,031
you'll know what I look like
if you touch my face.

251
00:25:32,783 --> 00:25:34,034
Come on.

252
00:25:34,785 --> 00:25:37,704
It's not respectful
to touch your face first.

253
00:25:43,043 --> 00:25:46,338
I asked you to start from the top.
You prefer to start at the bottom.

254
00:25:46,463 --> 00:25:48,215
That's fine with me.

255
00:25:48,966 --> 00:25:51,468
You've mastered
the flying technique.

256
00:25:54,805 --> 00:25:57,599
Your right hand
is skilled with a machete.

257
00:26:02,771 --> 00:26:05,899
Your left hand is powerful
with a bow and arrow.

258
00:26:12,322 --> 00:26:15,200
Your heart beats steadily,
you seem sincere.

259
00:26:16,201 --> 00:26:18,412
You can read me like a book.

260
00:26:18,996 --> 00:26:20,706
You're a brave man.

261
00:26:21,206 --> 00:26:23,333
I'm never shy around women.

262
00:26:28,130 --> 00:26:29,965
You're young, indeed.

263
00:26:38,891 --> 00:26:41,226
You know how to hold your drink.

264
00:26:43,103 --> 00:26:44,646
The soldiers are approaching.

265
00:26:45,355 --> 00:26:47,816
[Tense instrumental music]

266
00:27:05,918 --> 00:27:08,003
I've lost my dagger pouch.

267
00:27:17,137 --> 00:27:19,932
[Tense instrumental music intensifies]

268
00:27:32,194 --> 00:27:34,571
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

269
00:27:34,655 --> 00:27:36,323
[Horse snuffling]

270
00:27:48,919 --> 00:27:52,256
[Suspenseful instrumental music continues]

271
00:28:23,912 --> 00:28:26,290
[Dramatic instrumental music]

272
00:29:08,749 --> 00:29:10,250
[Soldier screaming]

273
00:29:10,667 --> 00:29:12,085
[Mei grunting]

274
00:29:37,611 --> 00:29:39,238
[Horse neighing]

275
00:29:49,456 --> 00:29:51,041
[Mei gasping]

276
00:30:03,887 --> 00:30:05,806
[Horse neighing in pain]

277
00:30:13,856 --> 00:30:16,733
[Dramatic instrumental music continues]

278
00:31:05,908 --> 00:31:07,534
[Mei screaming]

279
00:31:30,432 --> 00:31:32,976
[Solemn Oriental instrumental music]

280
00:31:52,496 --> 00:31:55,082
I'm sorry I was late.

281
00:32:19,731 --> 00:32:22,818
[Solemn Oriental instrumental music
continues]

282
00:33:33,597 --> 00:33:35,724
JIN: The Flying Daggers
are always moving.

283
00:33:35,807 --> 00:33:37,226
Where should we go?

284
00:33:37,851 --> 00:33:39,937
We just keep heading north.

285
00:33:40,854 --> 00:33:42,898
Just head north?

286
00:33:42,981 --> 00:33:44,816
They will come to us.

287
00:33:45,150 --> 00:33:47,736
The Flying Daggers
have many masters.

288
00:33:47,820 --> 00:33:49,905
Why did they send you
as an assassin?

289
00:33:49,988 --> 00:33:52,407
No one sent me. I came alone.

290
00:33:53,951 --> 00:33:58,163
JIN: As the old leader's daughter,
you should be more cautious.

291
00:33:58,997 --> 00:34:01,166
Have you considered
the consequences?

292
00:34:01,250 --> 00:34:04,253
I'll do anything
to avenge my father.

293
00:34:12,761 --> 00:34:14,137
Come here.

294
00:34:28,944 --> 00:34:31,905
These are men's clothes.
Put them on for now.

295
00:34:33,866 --> 00:34:34,867
[Clanking]

296
00:34:34,950 --> 00:34:37,244
I won't take advantage of you.

297
00:35:21,997 --> 00:35:24,583
[Clanking continues in the distance]

298
00:35:51,235 --> 00:35:53,070
MEI: Have you seen enough?

299
00:35:54,196 --> 00:35:56,323
<i>Please hand me the clothes.</i>

300
00:35:58,617 --> 00:36:00,369
JIN: You knew I was here?

301
00:36:01,036 --> 00:36:03,288
MEI: Master Wind wanders like the wind.

302
00:36:03,372 --> 00:36:05,624
MEI: I'd expect you to be anywhere.

303
00:36:30,524 --> 00:36:33,068
You look different in men's clothes.

304
00:36:33,735 --> 00:36:35,362
Do I look awful?

305
00:36:42,995 --> 00:36:45,789
I will tell all the girls
to wear men's clothes...

306
00:36:45,998 --> 00:36:49,042
the next time
I visit the Peony Pavilion.

307
00:37:07,227 --> 00:37:08,645
Now I know...

308
00:37:09,188 --> 00:37:11,356
you're not shy around women.

309
00:37:14,693 --> 00:37:16,528
You're not shy, either.

310
00:37:18,780 --> 00:37:20,365
How do you know?

311
00:37:22,993 --> 00:37:27,247
You knew I was watching you bathe,
yet you said nothing.

312
00:37:31,293 --> 00:37:33,128
You saved my life.

313
00:37:34,796 --> 00:37:36,965
You can look all you please.

314
00:37:49,978 --> 00:37:52,606
[Romantic Oriental instrumental music]

315
00:38:59,298 --> 00:39:01,550
JIN: I thought you were hot as fire.

316
00:39:02,092 --> 00:39:04,303
JIN: In fact, you're cool as water.

317
00:39:07,556 --> 00:39:09,766
MEI: I don't know you well enough.

318
00:39:12,436 --> 00:39:14,271
JIN: I really care for you.

319
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:21,653
MEI: A playboy like you,
are you ever for real?

320
00:39:24,531 --> 00:39:26,450
JIN: What if I am this time?

321
00:40:19,294 --> 00:40:21,129
Are our men close by?

322
00:40:21,213 --> 00:40:24,049
LEO: I'm sure today's fighting
has fooled Mei.

323
00:40:25,092 --> 00:40:28,303
Our men will ease off from now on.

324
00:40:29,388 --> 00:40:32,140
Good. That'll save me some arrows.

325
00:40:33,642 --> 00:40:34,977
Any clues?

326
00:40:35,477 --> 00:40:36,728
Not yet.

327
00:40:37,604 --> 00:40:39,565
Don't let her see through you.

328
00:40:39,648 --> 00:40:43,235
Don't worry.
I never fail at seducing a woman.

329
00:40:44,069 --> 00:40:45,571
She trusts me.

330
00:40:46,989 --> 00:40:50,159
I warn you, don't fall for her.

331
00:40:52,035 --> 00:40:53,871
What do you mean, fall?

332
00:40:54,788 --> 00:40:56,331
Fall into bed.

333
00:40:58,667 --> 00:41:01,461
Like her father,
she must be very cunning.

334
00:41:02,212 --> 00:41:03,839
Don't let her fool you.

335
00:41:03,922 --> 00:41:05,507
Don't be absurd.

336
00:41:06,758 --> 00:41:08,260
I'm in control.

337
00:41:09,136 --> 00:41:11,054
I have to get back now.

338
00:41:13,307 --> 00:41:16,476
Don't turn a game into
reality and ruin our plan.

339
00:41:17,227 --> 00:41:19,813
JIN: Who cares,
as long as the plan works.

340
00:41:39,833 --> 00:41:41,835
Shall we rest for a while?

341
00:41:42,878 --> 00:41:45,464
[Soft Oriental instrumental music]

342
00:41:47,549 --> 00:41:48,675
[Inhaling deeply]

343
00:41:48,759 --> 00:41:50,344
I smell flowers.

344
00:42:02,022 --> 00:42:05,275
[Romantic Oriental instrumental music]

345
00:42:07,319 --> 00:42:11,156
You told me you'd bring me
to where real flowers grow.

346
00:42:37,307 --> 00:42:40,936
[Romantic Oriental instrumental music
continues]

347
00:43:07,045 --> 00:43:09,214
Which is the most beautiful?

348
00:43:22,436 --> 00:43:23,979
How do I look?

349
00:43:24,146 --> 00:43:25,856
Pretty as a flower.

350
00:43:32,738 --> 00:43:34,698
Soldiers are approaching.

351
00:44:05,979 --> 00:44:07,856
[All grunting]

352
00:44:10,234 --> 00:44:12,569
- [Whispering] I'm on your side.
- You?

353
00:44:12,653 --> 00:44:15,447
JIN: I am a captain of the County.
SOLDIER: A captain?

354
00:44:17,157 --> 00:44:20,702
Nonsense.
You are the bastard who broke the jail.

355
00:44:23,288 --> 00:44:25,874
[Tense instrumental music]

356
00:45:01,243 --> 00:45:03,245
[Soldier screaming]

357
00:45:09,501 --> 00:45:12,588
[Tense instrumental music continues]

358
00:45:34,526 --> 00:45:36,069
[Mei screaming]

359
00:46:43,887 --> 00:46:46,223
You're wounded. Is it serious?

360
00:46:47,724 --> 00:46:48,767
No.

361
00:47:19,506 --> 00:47:21,675
[Music intensifies]

362
00:48:22,694 --> 00:48:24,488
[Soldier screaming in pain]

363
00:48:36,500 --> 00:48:38,919
Was it someone
from the Flying Daggers?

364
00:48:47,511 --> 00:48:49,137
It's not likely.

365
00:48:52,432 --> 00:48:53,725
Then who?

366
00:48:56,270 --> 00:48:57,771
I don't know.

367
00:49:01,733 --> 00:49:03,026
He's gone.

368
00:49:05,487 --> 00:49:08,323
I guess he doesn't want
to reveal himself.

369
00:49:08,782 --> 00:49:11,451
[Solemn Oriental instrumental music]

370
00:49:51,950 --> 00:49:55,204
This time,
I believe that you're for real.

371
00:49:59,917 --> 00:50:03,003
[Solemn Oriental instrumental music
continues]

372
00:50:46,630 --> 00:50:48,298
[Jin grunting]

373
00:50:56,056 --> 00:50:59,184
[Solemn Oriental instrumental music
continues]

374
00:51:08,652 --> 00:51:10,696
You've done enough for me.

375
00:51:11,864 --> 00:51:13,282
Please leave.

376
00:51:14,908 --> 00:51:16,743
Don't worry about me.

377
00:51:19,329 --> 00:51:22,583
We've come this far.
I can't leave you now.

378
00:51:28,589 --> 00:51:30,465
[Mei crying softly]

379
00:51:51,487 --> 00:51:53,989
I hope you're not seriously wounded.

380
00:51:54,740 --> 00:51:56,658
We agreed
there would be no more fights.

381
00:51:56,742 --> 00:51:59,036
Why did government soldiers turn up?

382
00:51:59,119 --> 00:52:02,873
The General sent them.
They don't know you.

383
00:52:03,665 --> 00:52:05,042
The General?

384
00:52:05,918 --> 00:52:08,337
How did the General get involved?

385
00:52:09,046 --> 00:52:11,882
This case is important.
I had to report it.

386
00:52:12,424 --> 00:52:14,468
The General is taking over.

387
00:52:16,845 --> 00:52:19,348
The soldiers
didn't have to be that aggressive.

388
00:52:19,431 --> 00:52:20,933
The General ordered it.

389
00:52:21,016 --> 00:52:24,061
He said we need real blood
to draw the Flying Daggers out.

390
00:52:24,144 --> 00:52:26,146
Even if the blood is mine?

391
00:52:27,314 --> 00:52:28,482
Jin...

392
00:52:30,067 --> 00:52:34,530
the soldiers' lives and our lives
are worth nothing to him.

393
00:52:36,657 --> 00:52:40,661
You don't know how I felt
as I killed our own men.

394
00:52:41,703 --> 00:52:44,748
I feel worse. I am tortured.

395
00:52:45,123 --> 00:52:46,291
You?

396
00:52:47,251 --> 00:52:48,877
I truly regret...

397
00:52:50,087 --> 00:52:52,005
taking on this mission.

398
00:52:52,172 --> 00:52:55,968
I've followed you all the way.
Endured many sleepless nights.

399
00:52:56,218 --> 00:53:00,556
LEO: My heart grows heavy
when I think about what lies ahead.

400
00:53:08,313 --> 00:53:11,233
Is there no other way to do this?

401
00:53:13,152 --> 00:53:14,903
The General said...

402
00:53:16,321 --> 00:53:20,492
it's the only way
to expose the Flying Daggers.

403
00:53:24,788 --> 00:53:28,125
Jin, you should know
there are more soldiers ahead.

404
00:53:29,543 --> 00:53:32,129
- What?
- The General sent them.

405
00:53:32,796 --> 00:53:34,840
They don't know you, either.

406
00:53:34,923 --> 00:53:36,592
You must stop them.

407
00:53:37,509 --> 00:53:39,553
There is nothing I can do.

408
00:53:41,972 --> 00:53:45,726
The order given to these soldiers...

409
00:53:46,226 --> 00:53:47,936
is ''fight to kill.''

410
00:53:49,771 --> 00:53:51,773
If you don't kill them...

411
00:53:52,649 --> 00:53:54,359
they will kill you.

412
00:53:57,738 --> 00:53:59,031
Take care.

413
00:54:14,796 --> 00:54:16,048
I quit.

414
00:54:58,006 --> 00:54:59,466
Where have you been?

415
00:55:04,304 --> 00:55:06,306
I have a question for you.

416
00:55:07,307 --> 00:55:09,726
- What question?
- Are you for real?

417
00:55:13,564 --> 00:55:15,190
What do you mean?

418
00:55:16,567 --> 00:55:18,735
Do you feel anything for me?

419
00:55:23,740 --> 00:55:25,742
Don't take this so seriously.

420
00:55:25,868 --> 00:55:27,369
I want to know.

421
00:55:29,371 --> 00:55:31,165
I'm a free spirit...

422
00:55:31,582 --> 00:55:34,251
like the wind, airways moving.

423
00:55:34,960 --> 00:55:36,461
The wind never thinks too much.

424
00:55:36,587 --> 00:55:39,006
I want the wind to stop and think.

425
00:55:39,089 --> 00:55:40,883
The wind cannot stop.

426
00:55:42,301 --> 00:55:43,886
Not even for me?

427
00:55:49,975 --> 00:55:53,103
The wind breezes through
without a trace.

428
00:55:58,066 --> 00:55:59,860
Now you understand...

429
00:56:00,319 --> 00:56:02,070
why I'm called Wind.

430
00:56:20,047 --> 00:56:23,884
Fine, go and be the wind.

431
00:56:25,177 --> 00:56:27,137
I don't need you anymore!

432
00:56:32,684 --> 00:56:34,311
[Wood clattering]

433
00:56:57,668 --> 00:57:01,004
I don't care if you're true or not.
I have to leave.

434
00:57:03,507 --> 00:57:05,259
I want to end this.

435
00:57:05,634 --> 00:57:07,386
Are you going alone?

436
00:57:09,429 --> 00:57:11,473
I'd like to be the wind for once.

437
00:57:11,557 --> 00:57:13,225
Where will you go?

438
00:57:13,559 --> 00:57:16,228
Who knows.
Whichever way the wind blows.

439
00:57:16,311 --> 00:57:18,438
Aren't you going back
to the Flying Daggers?

440
00:57:18,522 --> 00:57:20,566
Do you want me to go back?

441
00:57:24,111 --> 00:57:26,613
I've left them. Why would I return?

442
00:57:32,202 --> 00:57:34,329
Thank you
for all you've done for me.

443
00:57:48,844 --> 00:57:51,680
[Solemn Oriental instrumental music]

444
00:59:12,010 --> 00:59:15,097
[Solemn Oriental instrumental music
continues]

445
01:00:56,073 --> 01:00:57,616
[Soft clanking]

446
01:01:04,748 --> 01:01:06,250
[Mei grunting]

447
01:01:10,546 --> 01:01:12,130
[Mei screaming]

448
01:02:17,571 --> 01:02:19,615
[Soldiers panting]

449
01:02:32,211 --> 01:02:34,004
[Soldier screaming]

450
01:03:09,331 --> 01:03:11,708
[Dramatic instrumental music]

451
01:03:32,855 --> 01:03:34,481
- It's you.
- Go.

452
01:03:35,023 --> 01:03:37,818
[Romantic Oriental instrumental music]

453
01:04:14,688 --> 01:04:17,900
[Romantic Oriental instrumental music
continues]

454
01:05:25,008 --> 01:05:26,510
[Mei exclaims]

455
01:05:29,054 --> 01:05:31,390
[Dramatic instrumental music]

456
01:06:16,226 --> 01:06:19,062
You said the wind could not stop.

457
01:06:20,147 --> 01:06:22,941
A playful wind stops at will.

458
01:06:25,694 --> 01:06:27,821
You shouldn't have come back.

459
01:06:27,946 --> 01:06:29,406
I came back...

460
01:06:31,116 --> 01:06:32,367
for you.

461
01:06:36,538 --> 01:06:39,500
[Solemn Oriental instrumental music]

462
01:07:07,945 --> 01:07:09,530
[Daggers whooshing]

463
01:07:15,494 --> 01:07:17,704
[Soldiers exclaiming in pain]

464
01:07:24,461 --> 01:07:25,504
Nia!

465
01:07:33,303 --> 01:07:34,930
Mei, you're back.

466
01:07:46,316 --> 01:07:48,485
Who will believe
the madam of Peony Pavilion...

467
01:07:48,569 --> 01:07:50,988
is the leader of the Flying Daggers?

468
01:07:51,071 --> 01:07:53,740
I behaved badly that day.
Please forgive me.

469
01:07:53,824 --> 01:07:57,202
Did I look like a real madam?

470
01:07:57,494 --> 01:07:59,621
Very much so.

471
01:08:03,542 --> 01:08:05,502
What do you think of Mei?

472
01:08:06,253 --> 01:08:08,088
What do you mean?

473
01:08:08,505 --> 01:08:09,798
[Chuckling]

474
01:08:10,048 --> 01:08:13,260
I mean her personality, of course.

475
01:08:15,095 --> 01:08:16,889
She's passionate.

476
01:08:18,140 --> 01:08:19,266
Go on.

477
01:08:20,392 --> 01:08:23,061
She may be blind,
but she's very bright.

478
01:08:25,105 --> 01:08:27,232
Hardly anyone can match her.

479
01:08:27,483 --> 01:08:29,234
Not even I.

480
01:08:32,154 --> 01:08:34,198
Do you care for her?

481
01:08:34,907 --> 01:08:36,867
You are asking....

482
01:08:36,950 --> 01:08:38,911
A man and a girl travelling all alone.

483
01:08:38,994 --> 01:08:41,455
What else could I be talking about?

484
01:08:44,958 --> 01:08:46,752
Mei is a rare beauty.

485
01:08:47,419 --> 01:08:49,004
I care for her a lot.

486
01:08:49,087 --> 01:08:52,674
Then I shall act as the matchmaker
for you two to marry.

487
01:09:00,432 --> 01:09:03,185
Marriage is a big deal.
This is too sudden.

488
01:09:03,227 --> 01:09:05,229
She's not a good match for you?

489
01:09:05,312 --> 01:09:06,939
On the contrary.

490
01:09:07,231 --> 01:09:11,068
Mei is from a respectable family.
I'm just a humble swordsman.

491
01:09:11,527 --> 01:09:14,363
MADAM: Our old leader
loved his daughter dearly.

492
01:09:14,905 --> 01:09:16,240
Now I've become the new leader.

493
01:09:16,323 --> 01:09:18,992
MADAM: It's my duty
to find her a good husband.

494
01:09:19,284 --> 01:09:23,247
I haven't been able to find anyone
within the Flying Daggers...

495
01:09:23,372 --> 01:09:25,999
who would be a better choice
than you.

496
01:09:27,042 --> 01:09:28,627
What do you say?

497
01:09:32,923 --> 01:09:35,342
I accept your offer.

498
01:09:36,134 --> 01:09:40,097
Our House is much obliged to you.
You've done us a great favour.

499
01:09:42,391 --> 01:09:44,226
Please accept my gratitude.

500
01:09:44,309 --> 01:09:46,061
With much pleasure.

501
01:09:49,481 --> 01:09:50,983
[Jin grunting]

502
01:09:53,777 --> 01:09:55,988
What is going on?

503
01:10:17,676 --> 01:10:19,261
Where are our soldiers?

504
01:10:19,344 --> 01:10:21,054
They were ambushed.

505
01:10:24,308 --> 01:10:28,103
You were both plotting to catch me
by following Mei.

506
01:10:38,572 --> 01:10:41,241
[Dramatic Oriental instrumental music]

507
01:11:07,935 --> 01:11:09,561
You're not blind?

508
01:11:19,196 --> 01:11:21,657
Are you the old leader's daughter?

509
01:11:22,449 --> 01:11:24,409
He has a blind daughter.

510
01:11:24,910 --> 01:11:28,455
She doesn't know martial arts,
so I pretended to be her.

511
01:11:29,206 --> 01:11:31,416
MADAM: If you had known the truth...

512
01:11:31,959 --> 01:11:34,336
would you have followed her here?

513
01:11:40,676 --> 01:11:42,845
[Soft instrumental music]

514
01:11:45,139 --> 01:11:46,932
It's all been an act.

515
01:12:01,989 --> 01:12:03,740
Who are you really?

516
01:12:05,159 --> 01:12:06,660
My name is Mei.

517
01:12:06,952 --> 01:12:10,581
I'm just one of many girls in
the House of Flying Daggers.

518
01:12:15,544 --> 01:12:18,088
That's enough. Take him out.

519
01:12:27,181 --> 01:12:28,640
MADAM: You wait here.

520
01:12:28,807 --> 01:12:31,101
MADAM: I want to finish him off myself.

521
01:12:31,977 --> 01:12:33,061
Move.

522
01:12:53,582 --> 01:12:54,666
MADAM: Stop.

523
01:12:58,003 --> 01:13:00,172
MADAM: Do you have anything to say?

524
01:13:01,215 --> 01:13:03,467
You're not Nia, the new leader.

525
01:13:03,926 --> 01:13:05,427
[Madam scoffing]

526
01:13:05,594 --> 01:13:07,054
You're right.

527
01:13:07,262 --> 01:13:09,097
Of course I'm not Nia.

528
01:13:10,098 --> 01:13:12,643
Nia wouldn't show herself so easily.

529
01:13:15,062 --> 01:13:16,688
Who are you, then?

530
01:13:17,689 --> 01:13:19,274
That is not important.

531
01:13:19,358 --> 01:13:21,819
Nia sent me to finish this matter.

532
01:13:30,702 --> 01:13:32,871
You've done a good job, Leo.

533
01:13:35,123 --> 01:13:37,334
[Soft instrumental music]

534
01:13:37,417 --> 01:13:40,754
We've never met before,
but I know you by reputation.

535
01:13:41,839 --> 01:13:43,090
Three years ago...

536
01:13:43,173 --> 01:13:46,134
our old leader planted you as a mole
within the government.

537
01:13:46,218 --> 01:13:48,846
You've accomplished much
in that role.

538
01:13:50,973 --> 01:13:53,016
I failed to protect him...

539
01:13:54,560 --> 01:13:56,478
from being assassinated.

540
01:13:56,562 --> 01:13:59,565
MADAM: Nia knew
that you were away on duty.

541
01:13:59,648 --> 01:14:01,942
<i>There was nothing you could do.</i>

542
01:14:03,527 --> 01:14:05,821
I'm grateful for her understanding.

543
01:14:05,946 --> 01:14:10,367
MADAM: We need to win this battle
against the government troops.

544
01:14:11,326 --> 01:14:15,539
<i>You and Mei have successfully
set up a trap for the General.</i>

545
01:14:15,622 --> 01:14:16,915
<i>Well done.</i>

546
01:14:17,708 --> 01:14:20,169
I'll report to Nia
and have you rewarded.

547
01:14:20,252 --> 01:14:21,670
It's my duty.

548
01:14:23,130 --> 01:14:24,840
Please tell Nia...

549
01:14:25,424 --> 01:14:28,802
the General has led all his
best soldiers towards us.

550
01:14:29,219 --> 01:14:30,512
Be careful.

551
01:14:31,680 --> 01:14:34,516
Don't worry. Nia has a good plan.

552
01:14:36,185 --> 01:14:37,853
There is one thing
I don't understand.

553
01:14:37,936 --> 01:14:39,146
What's that?

554
01:14:39,229 --> 01:14:41,857
Who sent Mei on this mission?

555
01:14:42,107 --> 01:14:43,317
Nia did.

556
01:14:44,276 --> 01:14:46,737
Has Nia ever considered my feelings?

557
01:14:46,820 --> 01:14:48,489
What do you mean?

558
01:14:49,573 --> 01:14:52,034
I haven't seen Mei for three years.

559
01:14:52,242 --> 01:14:55,329
Now I have to watch her flirt
with another man.

560
01:14:55,704 --> 01:14:57,414
It's not the first time...

561
01:14:57,498 --> 01:15:00,751
Mei's been asked to use her beauty
to seduce a man.

562
01:15:03,462 --> 01:15:06,006
MADAM: I've heard about
your feelings for her.

563
01:15:06,089 --> 01:15:07,925
Do you still love her?

564
01:15:10,385 --> 01:15:11,887
We're facing a battle...

565
01:15:11,970 --> 01:15:14,097
that will decide
the fate of the Flying Daggers.

566
01:15:14,223 --> 01:15:15,724
<i>The troops are closing in.</i>

567
01:15:15,808 --> 01:15:18,018
<i>This is not the time for love.</i>

568
01:15:23,524 --> 01:15:24,858
All right.

569
01:15:26,026 --> 01:15:28,320
I will let you see Mei.

570
01:15:35,619 --> 01:15:38,539
[Soft instrumental music continues]

571
01:16:10,028 --> 01:16:12,489
[Dramatic Oriental instrumental music]

572
01:16:40,476 --> 01:16:43,479
[Dramatic Oriental instrumental music
resumes]

573
01:17:02,956 --> 01:17:04,750
You haven't changed.

574
01:17:05,876 --> 01:17:07,377
I'm still Mei.

575
01:17:11,507 --> 01:17:13,300
It's been three years.

576
01:17:13,967 --> 01:17:16,178
Finally, we're alone together.

577
01:17:17,387 --> 01:17:18,555
I know.

578
01:17:24,812 --> 01:17:27,648
You saved me
during the battle with the soldiers.

579
01:17:27,731 --> 01:17:29,066
Thank you.

580
01:17:29,942 --> 01:17:31,735
You don't need to thank me.

581
01:17:31,819 --> 01:17:34,613
I would do anything for you.

582
01:17:39,576 --> 01:17:40,786
I know.

583
01:17:41,453 --> 01:17:43,372
You've risked everything
going undercover...

584
01:17:43,455 --> 01:17:45,082
to win honour...

585
01:17:45,290 --> 01:17:46,959
and to impress me.

586
01:17:50,462 --> 01:17:52,297
You're the only one...

587
01:17:53,298 --> 01:17:55,050
who understands me.

588
01:18:03,433 --> 01:18:05,727
I was all alone for three years.

589
01:18:05,811 --> 01:18:08,230
<i>You were in my mind
every single moment.</i>

590
01:18:08,313 --> 01:18:12,609
LEO: My love for you was all
I had to keep me going.

591
01:18:25,831 --> 01:18:28,584
[Romantic Oriental instrumental music]

592
01:19:24,181 --> 01:19:26,016
[Mei sobbing softly]

593
01:20:12,312 --> 01:20:15,440
[Romantic Oriental instrumental music
continues]

594
01:21:10,662 --> 01:21:12,247
Do you love him?

595
01:21:23,634 --> 01:21:25,302
You knew the plan.

596
01:21:27,763 --> 01:21:30,474
It was only an act
between you and him.

597
01:21:44,947 --> 01:21:47,241
There is no future for you two.

598
01:21:49,451 --> 01:21:51,119
Do you understand?

599
01:22:11,348 --> 01:22:13,392
[Mei grunting in protest]

600
01:22:22,651 --> 01:22:24,653
[Leo grunting angrily]

601
01:22:32,369 --> 01:22:34,621
[Dramatic instrumental music]

602
01:22:44,131 --> 01:22:45,215
LEO: Nia!

603
01:22:46,675 --> 01:22:50,512
You can't force a woman
against her will.

604
01:22:52,764 --> 01:22:54,933
<i>Do not pull this dagger out.</i>

605
01:22:55,267 --> 01:22:58,145
I'm sending you back
to keep spying for us.

606
01:22:58,187 --> 01:23:02,733
You will be more convincing
with a dagger in your back.

607
01:23:05,444 --> 01:23:06,945
You must leave immediately.

608
01:23:08,655 --> 01:23:09,990
LEO: Yes, ma'am.

609
01:23:12,659 --> 01:23:15,829
[Solemn Oriental instrumental music]

610
01:23:21,376 --> 01:23:25,047
I have sacrificed three years
for you.

611
01:23:26,048 --> 01:23:29,009
LEO: How could you love Jin
after just three days?

612
01:23:47,361 --> 01:23:49,696
NIA: Mei, I also have a task for you.

613
01:23:50,823 --> 01:23:53,116
Jin is of no use to us anymore.

614
01:23:53,742 --> 01:23:56,620
Take him out and kill him.

615
01:23:59,832 --> 01:24:02,584
<i>Leo plays a crucial role for us.</i>

616
01:24:03,085 --> 01:24:05,337
<i>We can't let Jin ruin our plan.</i>

617
01:24:06,171 --> 01:24:07,965
You must kill him...

618
01:24:08,924 --> 01:24:11,593
to prevent any future trouble.

619
01:24:14,972 --> 01:24:16,723
You know our rules.

620
01:24:18,100 --> 01:24:19,434
MEI: Yes, ma'am.

621
01:24:21,895 --> 01:24:24,940
[Solemn Oriental instrumental music
continues]

622
01:25:15,240 --> 01:25:16,700
I left you...

623
01:25:16,867 --> 01:25:18,911
in order to save your life.

624
01:25:19,244 --> 01:25:21,288
But you still followed me.

625
01:25:21,497 --> 01:25:23,332
<i>Please don't blame me.</i>

626
01:25:24,541 --> 01:25:26,418
MEI: If your plan succeeded...

627
01:25:26,502 --> 01:25:28,462
many in the Flying Daggers
would die.

628
01:25:28,587 --> 01:25:30,798
You wouldn't let me go, either.

629
01:25:31,507 --> 01:25:33,675
It would be me on my knees...

630
01:25:34,468 --> 01:25:36,011
waiting to die.

631
01:25:40,766 --> 01:25:42,184
You're right.

632
01:25:43,018 --> 01:25:44,353
If I won...

633
01:25:45,687 --> 01:25:47,523
I wouldn't let you go.

634
01:26:07,376 --> 01:26:10,170
[Romantic instrumental music]

635
01:26:28,605 --> 01:26:31,400
[Romantic instrumental music continues]

636
01:27:21,867 --> 01:27:24,786
[Romantic instrumental music intensifies]

637
01:27:44,515 --> 01:27:47,476
[Solemn instrumental music]

638
01:27:51,230 --> 01:27:52,272
Go.

639
01:27:56,276 --> 01:27:58,737
How will you explain this to Nia?

640
01:28:02,491 --> 01:28:04,201
That's my business.

641
01:28:06,787 --> 01:28:08,872
Why don't you come with me?

642
01:28:24,555 --> 01:28:27,141
Deep in your heart,
you have a secret.

643
01:28:33,272 --> 01:28:34,606
I guess...

644
01:28:35,816 --> 01:28:38,777
there is a man
you find hard to leave behind.

645
01:28:43,365 --> 01:28:46,785
Yes, a man who's saved my life
many times.

646
01:28:51,165 --> 01:28:54,001
Was it he who helped us
in the last battle?

647
01:28:55,294 --> 01:28:56,336
Yes.

648
01:29:00,716 --> 01:29:03,051
Then he has saved my life, too.

649
01:29:08,140 --> 01:29:09,975
Do you still love him?

650
01:29:12,019 --> 01:29:14,813
[Solemn instrumental music continues]

651
01:29:22,112 --> 01:29:24,531
When can we see each other again?

652
01:29:27,618 --> 01:29:28,911
We cannot.

653
01:29:32,748 --> 01:29:35,042
We belong to two opposing sides.

654
01:29:35,667 --> 01:29:37,419
If we meet again...

655
01:29:38,795 --> 01:29:40,923
one of us will have to die.

656
01:29:48,430 --> 01:29:50,933
[Solemn instrumental music swells]

657
01:30:29,513 --> 01:30:31,807
JIN: A decisive battle is imminent.

658
01:30:33,100 --> 01:30:35,894
JIN: You and I are just pawns
on a chessboard.

659
01:30:36,270 --> 01:30:38,605
<i>Nobody cares if we live or die.</i>

660
01:30:42,943 --> 01:30:45,904
Let's go away together
and roam the world...

661
01:30:45,988 --> 01:30:47,739
as free as the wind.

662
01:30:52,244 --> 01:30:54,913
We'll wander around alone.

663
01:30:55,122 --> 01:30:59,042
MEI: Come and go without a trace,
like a playful wind.

664
01:30:59,626 --> 01:31:02,421
No, a carefree wind.

665
01:31:05,757 --> 01:31:07,426
Just you and me.

666
01:31:12,473 --> 01:31:14,266
Come with me, please.

667
01:31:30,657 --> 01:31:33,619
[Melancholic Oriental instrumental music]

668
01:32:34,972 --> 01:32:38,433
[Melancholic Oriental instrumental music
continues]

669
01:34:00,432 --> 01:34:03,977
[Melancholic Oriental instrumental music
intensifies]

670
01:34:32,923 --> 01:34:34,174
[Groans]

671
01:34:47,813 --> 01:34:49,857
[Whimpering in pain]

672
01:35:16,383 --> 01:35:18,260
Are you going with him?

673
01:35:19,553 --> 01:35:22,014
[Sentimental instrumental music]

674
01:35:23,765 --> 01:35:25,225
Why?

675
01:35:33,734 --> 01:35:35,777
You're the love of my life.

676
01:35:40,032 --> 01:35:42,201
You don't have to love me...

677
01:35:43,202 --> 01:35:45,454
but you can never go with him.

678
01:35:54,129 --> 01:35:55,923
Otherwise you'll die.

679
01:36:01,553 --> 01:36:02,721
Mei...

680
01:36:06,642 --> 01:36:08,852
you've forced me to kill you.

681
01:36:14,983 --> 01:36:16,401
I knew...

682
01:36:17,820 --> 01:36:19,321
you would do this.

683
01:36:24,117 --> 01:36:26,912
You knew and you went anyway. Why?

684
01:36:27,454 --> 01:36:28,956
Why did you go?

685
01:36:29,498 --> 01:36:31,834
Why did you go? Why?

686
01:36:37,172 --> 01:36:38,590
To be free...

687
01:36:39,466 --> 01:36:40,968
Like the wind.

688
01:36:50,477 --> 01:36:52,604
[Screaming hysterically]

689
01:37:06,410 --> 01:37:08,996
[Fast-paced instrumental music]

690
01:37:59,671 --> 01:38:00,756
Mei.

691
01:38:02,049 --> 01:38:03,133
JIN: Mei!

692
01:38:13,018 --> 01:38:14,061
JIN: Mei!

693
01:38:14,269 --> 01:38:15,395
[Whispering] Turn....

694
01:38:16,188 --> 01:38:17,314
What?

695
01:38:19,691 --> 01:38:20,818
MEI: Turn....

696
01:38:20,901 --> 01:38:22,319
Turn around?

697
01:38:24,613 --> 01:38:27,074
MEI: Look behind you.

698
01:38:31,411 --> 01:38:32,788
[Leo screaming]

699
01:39:09,324 --> 01:39:11,577
You're a member of the Flying Daggers.

700
01:39:12,286 --> 01:39:13,704
You're right.

701
01:39:14,913 --> 01:39:16,456
You're the one who loves Mei?

702
01:39:16,540 --> 01:39:19,376
Yes, I love her truly...

703
01:39:20,085 --> 01:39:22,504
while you are only playing a game.

704
01:39:22,754 --> 01:39:25,632
If you love her, why kill her?

705
01:39:25,716 --> 01:39:28,802
It's all your fault.

706
01:39:29,720 --> 01:39:31,013
My fault?

707
01:39:31,555 --> 01:39:36,351
I warned you, but you wouldn't listen.

708
01:39:39,688 --> 01:39:42,149
She has betrayed me because of you.

709
01:39:42,441 --> 01:39:43,942
You must die.

710
01:39:46,737 --> 01:39:47,821
Fine.

711
01:39:48,197 --> 01:39:50,991
You kill Mei, you must die, too.

712
01:39:51,200 --> 01:39:52,826
[Both screaming]

713
01:40:27,110 --> 01:40:28,987
[Sombre music]

714
01:40:46,547 --> 01:40:48,340
[Thunder rumbling]

715
01:40:54,638 --> 01:40:57,349
[Jin and Leo grunting in the distance]

716
01:41:18,996 --> 01:41:20,706
[Both screaming]

717
01:41:38,640 --> 01:41:40,225
[Screaming hysterically]

718
01:41:48,484 --> 01:41:50,777
[Sombre music continues]

719
01:42:27,981 --> 01:42:30,317
[Sombre music intensifies]

720
01:42:41,703 --> 01:42:43,747
[Both screaming]

721
01:43:45,767 --> 01:43:47,352
[Groaning]

722
01:43:50,981 --> 01:43:54,067
[Melancholic Oriental instrumental music]

723
01:44:00,949 --> 01:44:02,034
Mei.

724
01:44:14,171 --> 01:44:15,506
Let him go.

725
01:44:18,926 --> 01:44:20,594
If you kill him...

726
01:44:22,471 --> 01:44:24,765
I'll kill you with this dagger.

727
01:44:25,015 --> 01:44:27,267
Mei! Don't pull the dagger out!

728
01:44:27,601 --> 01:44:31,480
JIN: If you do, your blood will drain
and you will die.

729
01:44:33,982 --> 01:44:35,692
You must not do it!

730
01:44:37,277 --> 01:44:40,739
[Melancholic Oriental instrumental music
continues]

731
01:44:53,794 --> 01:44:54,962
Mei...

732
01:44:55,379 --> 01:44:57,047
I'm closer to him.

733
01:44:57,339 --> 01:44:59,133
<i>He will hit me first.</i>

734
01:44:59,883 --> 01:45:01,677
You cannot save me...

735
01:45:03,178 --> 01:45:04,805
with your dagger.

736
01:45:15,440 --> 01:45:19,236
[Melancholic Oriental instrumental music
continues]

737
01:46:17,294 --> 01:46:19,004
[Groaning]

738
01:46:49,117 --> 01:46:50,202
Mei!

739
01:47:02,506 --> 01:47:03,882
Mei!

740
01:47:06,927 --> 01:47:08,846
[Sobbing]

741
01:47:18,188 --> 01:47:20,399
You shouldn't have come back.

742
01:47:24,278 --> 01:47:25,779
I came back...

743
01:47:27,364 --> 01:47:28,991
for you, my love.

744
01:47:47,885 --> 01:47:49,720
[Jin sobbing]

745
01:47:56,518 --> 01:47:58,437
[Thunder rumbling]

746
01:48:17,039 --> 01:48:19,333
[Wind howling]

747
01:48:34,723 --> 01:48:38,560
JIN: [Singing] A rare beauty in the North

748
01:48:40,395 --> 01:48:44,024
<i>She's the finest lady on earth</i>

749
01:48:46,026 --> 01:48:50,113
<i>A glance from her
the whole city goes down</i>

750
01:48:51,824 --> 01:48:56,203
<i>A second glance
leaves the whole nation in ruins</i>

751
01:48:57,704 --> 01:49:00,082
There exists no city or nation

752
01:49:00,791 --> 01:49:04,920
that has been more cherished

753
01:49:06,839 --> 01:49:11,301
<i>than a beauty like this</i>

754
01:49:12,928 --> 01:49:16,348
[Melancholic music]

755
01:49:51,341 --> 01:49:53,969
[Melancholic music continues]

756
01:50:32,341 --> 01:50:35,219
[Melancholic music continues]

757
01:51:11,547 --> 01:51:13,799
[Melancholic music continues]

758
01:52:15,360 --> 01:52:18,322
[Melancholic music continues]

